cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network design and routing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the minimum cost network design problem. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers the capacity of the network to route traffic demand matrices. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may be relevant as the paper discusses the impact of different routing models on network design. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) may be relevant as the paper deals with polytopes and their impact on network design.
